cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with multilingual neural machine translation models and their representations. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses Singular Value Canonical Correlation Analysis (SVCCA), a representation similarity framework, to compare representations across different languages, layers, and models. Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with transfer learning and cross-lingual transfer. It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural machine translation models. Finally, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it uses a similarity framework to analyze representations.
